\li{\code{\startverb publication.mplstyle\stopverb}: General publication quality}
\li{\code{\startverb nature.mplstyle\stopverb}: Nature journal specifications}
\li{\code{\startverb presentation.mplstyle\stopverb}: Larger fonts for posters/slides}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow Summary}
\p{\strong{Recommended workflow for creating publication figures:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Plan}: Determine target journal, figure type, and content}
\li{\strong{Configure}: Apply appropriate style for journal}
\li{\strong{Create}: Build figure with proper labels, colors, statistics}
\li{\strong{Verify}: Check size, fonts, colors, accessibility}
\li{\strong{Export}: Save in required formats}
\li{\strong{Review}: View at final size in manuscript context}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Pitfalls to Avoid}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Font too small}: Text unreadable when printed at final size}
\li{\strong{JPEG format}: Never use JPEG for graphs/plots (creates artifacts)}
\li{\startverb **Red-green colors**: ~8% of males cannot distinguish\stopverb}
\li{\strong{Low resolution}: Pixelated figures in publication}
\li{\strong{Missing units}: Always label axes with units}
\li{\strong{3D effects}: Distorts perception, avoid completely}
\li{\strong{Chart junk}: Remove unnecessary gridlines, decorations}
\li{\strong{Truncated axes}: Start bar charts at zero unless scientifically justified}
\li{\strong{Inconsistent styling}: Different fonts/colors across figures in same manuscript}
\li{\strong{No error bars}: Always show uncertainty}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Final Checklist}
\p{Before submitting figures, verify:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Resolution meets journal requirements (300+ DPI)}
\li{[ ] File format is correct (vector for plots, TIFF for images)}
\li{[ ] Figure size matches journal specifications}
\li{[ ] All text readable at final size (≥6 pt)}
\li{[ ] Colors are colorblind-friendly}
\li{[ ] Figure works in grayscale}
\li{[ ] All axes labeled with units}
\li{[ ] Error bars present with definition in caption}
\li{[ ] Panel labels present and consistent}
\li{[ ] No chart junk or 3D effects}
\li{[ ] Fonts consistent across all figures}
\li{[ ] Statistical significance clearly marked}
\li{[ ] Legend is clear and complete}
}

\p{Use this skill to ensure scientific figures meet the highest publication standards while remaining accessible to all readers.}
}
}